CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1960, pg. 21, reads: "Everybody's Happy - There wasn't a sad face in all of Pittsburgh Sunday night as the Pittsburgh Pirates, new National League champions, took part in a gigantic victory celebration, following the team's arrival from Milwaukee. Enjoying the festivities from convertibles are... in pictures on the right is outfielder Joe Christopher, riding with Billy Virdon and his wife. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Joe Christopher and Bill Virdon, riding in back of convertible car in parade for 1960 National League Championship, Downtown
